list.item:
the purely Japanese North China Development Company,
                                    capitalized at yen 500,000,000 will be the chief organ of
                                    exploitation;

a representative of the North China Development Company will
                                    participate in the direction of each of the Sino-Japanese
                                    companies;

the company controlling railways will receive part of its
                                    capital from the South Manchuria Railway Company and will be run
                                    by personnel formerly serving in that company;
